## Objective
Fix Bug 1: user messages vanish from history when Relay is enabled because `transcript-parser.ts:231` discards the entire string (including actual user content) when it starts with `<relay_context>`.

## Implementation

### 1. Create `stripRelayContext()` helper in transcript-parser.ts

Add this exported helper function above `parseTranscript()`:

```typescript
/**
 * Strip relay context wrapper, returning the user content or null if pure metadata.
 *
 * @param text - Raw message text potentially wrapped in relay_context tags
 * @returns The user content after the closing tag, or null if pure metadata/malformed
 * @internal Exported for testing only.
 */
export function stripRelayContext(text: string): string | null {
  if (!text.startsWith('<relay_context>')) return text;
  const closingTag = '</relay_context>';
  const idx = text.indexOf(closingTag);
  if (idx === -1) return null; // Malformed, no closing tag
  const content = text.slice(idx + closingTag.length).trim();
  return content || null; // Empty content = pure metadata
}
```

### 2. Replace the `continue` at line 231 with relay context stripping

Change the block at line 230-233 from:
```typescript
// Filter relay metadata injected by ClaudeCodeAdapter — never user-authored content
if (text.startsWith('<relay_context>')) {
  continue;
}
```

To:
```typescript
// Strip relay context wrapper, preserving the actual user content after </relay_context>
if (text.startsWith('<relay_context>')) {
  const userContent = stripRelayContext(text);
  if (!userContent) continue; // Pure metadata or malformed
  text = userContent; // Fall through to process as normal user message
}
```

Note: `text` is declared with `const` on line 224 (`const text = ...`). Change it to `let text = ...` to allow reassignment.

### 3. Unit Tests

Add to `apps/server/src/services/__tests__/transcript-parser.test.ts`:

```typescript
describe('stripRelayContext', () => {
  it('returns original text when no relay_context prefix', () => {
    expect(stripRelayContext('Hello world')).toBe('Hello world');
  });

  it('returns user content after closing tag', () => {
    const text = '<relay_context>\nAgent-ID: abc\nSubject: test\n</relay_context>\n\nWrite a bubble sort';
    expect(stripRelayContext(text)).toBe('Write a bubble sort');
  });

  it('returns null for pure relay metadata (no content after closing tag)', () => {
    const text = '<relay_context>\nAgent-ID: abc\n</relay_context>';
    expect(stripRelayContext(text)).toBeNull();
  });

  it('returns null for malformed relay_context (no closing tag)', () => {
    const text = '<relay_context>\nAgent-ID: abc\nno closing tag';
    expect(stripRelayContext(text)).toBeNull();
  });

  it('handles multiple paragraphs of user content after closing tag', () => {
    const text = '<relay_context>\nAgent-ID: abc\n</relay_context>\n\nParagraph 1\n\nParagraph 2';
    expect(stripRelayContext(text)).toBe('Paragraph 1\n\nParagraph 2');
  });

  it('preserves command-like text after relay context', () => {
    const text = '<relay_context>\nAgent-ID: abc\n</relay_context>\n\n/help';
    expect(stripRelayContext(text)).toBe('/help');
  });
});

describe('parseTranscript relay context handling', () => {
  it('strips relay_context wrapper and preserves user content in history', () => {
    const lines = [
      JSON.stringify({
        type: 'user',
        message: {
          content: '<relay_context>\nAgent-ID: 9c99edf1\nSubject: relay.agent.test\n</relay_context>\n\nWrite a JavaScript bubble sort function with comments',
        },
        uuid: 'msg-1',
      }),
    ];
    const result = parseTranscript(lines);
    expect(result).toHaveLength(1);
    expect(result[0].role).toBe('user');
    expect(result[0].content).toBe('Write a JavaScript bubble sort function with comments');
  });

  it('skips pure relay metadata with no user content', () => {
    const lines = [
      JSON.stringify({
        type: 'user',
        message: { content: '<relay_context>\nAgent-ID: abc\n</relay_context>' },
        uuid: 'msg-1',
      }),
    ];
    const result = parseTranscript(lines);
    expect(result).toHaveLength(0);
  });
});
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- `stripRelayContext('text without prefix')` returns the original text
- `stripRelayContext('<relay_context>...metadata...</relay_context>\n\nUser msg')` returns `'User msg'`
- `stripRelayContext('<relay_context>...metadata...</relay_context>')` returns `null`
- `stripRelayContext('<relay_context>no closing tag')` returns `null`
- `parseTranscript()` produces a user message with correct content when relay_context wraps the actual user text
- `parseTranscript()` skips lines that are pure relay metadata
- All existing transcript-parser tests continue to pass

## Objective
Fix Bug 2: When the agent calls a Skill, the SDK generates a user message with both `tool_result` and `text` content blocks. The text blocks are internal SDK expansion content (skill prompts), not user-authored. Currently `transcript-parser.ts` lines 187-220 render these text parts as user messages when `textParts.length > 0`.

## Implementation

In `apps/server/src/services/session/transcript-parser.ts`, replace the block at lines 187-194:

```typescript
// BEFORE:
if (hasToolResult && textParts.length === 0) {
  if (parsed.toolUseResult?.commandName) {
    const cmdName = '/' + parsed.toolUseResult.commandName.replace(/^\//, '');
    pendingCommand = { commandName: cmdName, commandArgs: pendingSkillArgs || '' };
    pendingSkillArgs = null;
  }
  continue;
}
```

With:

```typescript
// AFTER:
// When tool_result blocks are present, any text blocks are SDK-internal
// (skill expansion prompts, system context), never user-authored content.
// Process tool results but suppress the text parts.
if (hasToolResult) {
  if (parsed.toolUseResult?.commandName) {
    const cmdName = '/' + parsed.toolUseResult.commandName.replace(/^\//, '');
    pendingCommand = { commandName: cmdName, commandArgs: pendingSkillArgs || '' };
    pendingSkillArgs = null;
  }
  continue;
}
```

The key change: remove the `&& textParts.length === 0` condition. If `hasToolResult` is true, we always skip to the next line — any `textParts` in the same JSONL entry are SDK-injected content.

## Unit Tests

Add to `apps/server/src/services/__tests__/transcript-parser.test.ts`:

```typescript
describe('parseTranscript Skill tool_result suppression', () => {
  it('suppresses text blocks when tool_result is present in same message', () => {
    const lines = [
      // Assistant calls Skill tool
      JSON.stringify({
        type: 'assistant',
        message: {
          content: [
            {
              type: 'tool_use',
              id: 'tool-1',
              name: 'Skill',
              input: { skill: 'test-skill', args: 'arg1' },
            },
          ],
        },
        uuid: 'msg-1',
      }),
      // User message with tool_result AND text blocks (SDK skill expansion)
      JSON.stringify({
        type: 'user',
        message: {
          content: [
            { type: 'tool_result', tool_use_id: 'tool-1', content: 'skill output' },
            { type: 'text', text: 'Internal SDK skill expansion prompt that should not appear' },
          ],
        },
        uuid: 'msg-2',
      }),
    ];
    const result = parseTranscript(lines);
    // Should have assistant message with tool call, but NO user message for the expansion text
    const userMessages = result.filter((m) => m.role === 'user');
    expect(userMessages).toHaveLength(0);
  });

  it('preserves Skill tool call card after tool_result suppression', () => {
    const lines = [
      JSON.stringify({
        type: 'assistant',
        message: {
          content: [
            {
              type: 'tool_use',
              id: 'tool-1',
              name: 'Skill',
              input: { skill: 'test-skill' },
            },
          ],
        },
        uuid: 'msg-1',
      }),
      JSON.stringify({
        type: 'user',
        message: {
          content: [
            { type: 'tool_result', tool_use_id: 'tool-1', content: 'skill output' },
            { type: 'text', text: 'expansion text' },
          ],
        },
        uuid: 'msg-2',
      }),
    ];
    const result = parseTranscript(lines);
    const assistantMsg = result.find((m) => m.role === 'assistant');
    expect(assistantMsg?.toolCalls).toBeDefined();
    expect(assistantMsg!.toolCalls![0].toolName).toBe('Skill');
    expect(assistantMsg!.toolCalls![0].result).toBe('skill output');
  });

  it('handles multiple tool_result blocks in single user message', () => {
    const lines = [
      JSON.stringify({
        type: 'assistant',
        message: {
          content: [
            { type: 'tool_use', id: 'tool-1', name: 'ToolA', input: {} },
            { type: 'tool_use', id: 'tool-2', name: 'ToolB', input: {} },
          ],
        },
        uuid: 'msg-1',
      }),
      JSON.stringify({
        type: 'user',
        message: {
          content: [
            { type: 'tool_result', tool_use_id: 'tool-1', content: 'result A' },
            { type: 'tool_result', tool_use_id: 'tool-2', content: 'result B' },
            { type: 'text', text: 'should be suppressed' },
          ],
        },
        uuid: 'msg-2',
      }),
    ];
    const result = parseTranscript(lines);
    const userMessages = result.filter((m) => m.role === 'user');
    expect(userMessages).toHaveLength(0);
  });
});
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- When a user message contains `tool_result` blocks, any `text` blocks in the same message are NOT rendered as user messages
- The tool call itself still appears in the assistant message's `toolCalls` array with the correct result
- Existing tool_result handling (result assignment to toolCallMap/toolCallPartMap) is unaffected
- `pendingCommand` is still set correctly for Skill tool results with `commandName`
- All existing transcript-parser tests continue to pass

## Objective
Fix Bug 4: `sessions.ts:351` passes the raw Agent-ID to `registerClient()` without translating to the SDK-Session-ID. The broadcaster creates a file watcher for `{agentId}.jsonl` which doesn't exist (the file is `{sdkSessionId}.jsonl`), causing watcher failures and 503 floods.

## Implementation

In `apps/server/src/routes/sessions.ts`, modify the SSE stream route handler at line 351.

### 1. Get a reference to agentManager

The route handler already has access to `req.app.locals`. Check how other routes in the same file access `agentManager`. The sessions route factory likely receives it as a parameter or it's on `app.locals`.

### 2. Apply SDK-Session-ID translation

Change line 351 from:
```typescript
sessionBroadcaster.registerClient(sessionId, cwd, res, clientId);
```

To:
```typescript
const agentManager = req.app.locals.agentManager;
const sdkSessionId = agentManager.getSdkSessionId(sessionId) ?? sessionId;
sessionBroadcaster.registerClient(sdkSessionId, cwd, res, clientId);
```

This is the same pattern used by the GET `/api/sessions/:id/messages` endpoint in the same file, which already does this translation. The `getSdkSessionId()` method is an O(1) map lookup on the existing `sdkSessionIndex` in agent-manager.

If `agentManager` is not available on `req.app.locals`, check how the route file accesses it — it may be passed via the router factory function. Look at the top of `sessions.ts` for the factory signature and adjust accordingly.

## Unit Tests

Add to or create `apps/server/src/routes/__tests__/sessions.test.ts` (or the existing broadcaster test file):

```typescript
describe('SSE stream registration', () => {
  it('translates agent-ID to SDK session ID before registering client', () => {
    // Setup: mock agentManager.getSdkSessionId to return a translated ID
    const mockAgentManager = {
      getSdkSessionId: vi.fn().mockReturnValue('sdk-session-uuid'),
    };
    const mockBroadcaster = {
      registerClient: vi.fn(),
    };

    // The translated SDK session ID should be passed to registerClient,
    // not the raw agent-ID from the URL parameter
    // Verify: registerClient was called with 'sdk-session-uuid', not 'agent-id-from-url'
    expect(mockBroadcaster.registerClient).toHaveBeenCalledWith(
      'sdk-session-uuid',
      expect.any(String),
      expect.anything(),
      expect.anything(),
    );
  });

  it('falls back to original session ID when no SDK mapping exists', () => {
    const mockAgentManager = {
      getSdkSessionId: vi.fn().mockReturnValue(undefined),
    };
    // Verify: registerClient was called with the original sessionId
  });
});
```

Note: The exact test setup depends on how the route is structured (factory function vs direct export). Adapt the mocking strategy accordingly.

## Acceptance Criteria
- `registerClient()` receives the SDK session ID (the one matching the JSONL filename) rather than the raw agent/URL session ID
- When `getSdkSessionId()` returns `undefined` (no mapping), the original session ID is used as fallback
- File watchers created by the broadcaster target the correct `.jsonl` file on disk
- No 503 errors from mismatched watcher paths

## Objective
Fix Bug 3: SSE `done` event still fails to reach the client ~20% of the time. Add a client-side staleness detector as defense-in-depth so the client never hangs indefinitely.

## Implementation

In `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/model/use-chat-session.ts`, add a staleness timeout mechanism when relay is enabled.

### 1. Add constant

```typescript
/** Timeout (ms) after last SSE event before polling session status as fallback. */
const DONE_STALENESS_MS = 15_000;
```

### 2. Add staleness timer logic inside the streaming handler

Within the SSE event processing loop (the part that handles `text_delta`, `tool_call_start`, etc.), add timer management:

```typescript
let stalenessTimer: ReturnType<typeof setTimeout> | null = null;

const clearStalenessTimer = () => {
  if (stalenessTimer) {
    clearTimeout(stalenessTimer);
    stalenessTimer = null;
  }
};

const resetStalenessTimer = () => {
  clearStalenessTimer();
  stalenessTimer = setTimeout(async () => {
    // Check if session has completed on the backend
    try {
      const session = await transport.getSession(sessionId, cwd);
      if (session && !session.isStreaming) {
        // Backend completed but we missed the done event
        setStatus('idle');
        queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['messages', sessionId] });
      }
    } catch {
      // Network error — don't change state, timer will re-fire on next event
    }
  }, DONE_STALENESS_MS);
};
```

### 3. Call resetStalenessTimer on each received event

In the event processing switch/if block, after processing each `text_delta`, `tool_call_start`, `tool_call_delta`, `tool_call_end`, `tool_result` event, call `resetStalenessTimer()`.

### 4. Clear timer on `done` event and on cleanup

In the `done` event handler, call `clearStalenessTimer()`. Also clear in the cleanup/finally block:

```typescript
// In finally or cleanup:
clearStalenessTimer();
```

### 5. Only activate when relay is enabled

Wrap the timer logic with a check: only call `resetStalenessTimer()` if `relayEnabled` is true (or from the `useRelayEnabled()` hook). When relay is disabled, the `done` event delivery is reliable and no staleness detection is needed.

## Unit Tests

Add to `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/__tests__/use-chat-session.test.ts`:

```typescript
describe('staleness detector', () => {
  beforeEach(() => {
    vi.useFakeTimers();
  });

  afterEach(() => {
    vi.useRealTimers();
  });

  it('transitions to idle when backend completed but done event was missed', async () => {
    // Setup: mock transport.getSession to return a completed (non-streaming) session
    const mockTransport = createMockTransport();
    mockTransport.getSession = vi.fn().mockResolvedValue({ isStreaming: false });

    // Start a streaming session, receive some text_delta events
    // Advance timer by 15000ms without any new events
    vi.advanceTimersByTime(15_000);

    // Verify: status transitions to 'idle'
    // Verify: queryClient.invalidateQueries was called for messages
  });

  it('resets timer on each received event (does not fire during active streaming)', async () => {
    // Start streaming, receive events every 5 seconds
    // Advance timer by 14 seconds, send an event, advance by 14 seconds again
    // Verify: staleness callback was NOT called (timer kept resetting)
  });

  it('clears timer when done event is received', async () => {
    // Start streaming, receive done event
    // Advance timer by 20 seconds
    // Verify: staleness callback was NOT called
  });
});
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- When relay is enabled and no SSE events arrive for 15 seconds during an active stream, the client polls the backend session status
- If the backend reports the session is complete (not streaming), the client transitions to idle and refreshes messages
- The timer resets on every received SSE event, so it never fires during normal streaming
- The timer is cleared on `done` event receipt and on component cleanup
- When relay is disabled, no staleness timer is active
- No memory leaks (timer always cleaned up)

## Objective
Refactor `transcript-parser.ts` to reduce complexity: extract `applyToolResult()` and `emitPendingCommand()` helpers to eliminate duplicated code, and define `SDK_TOOL_NAMES` constants in the shared package to replace magic strings.

## Implementation

### 1. Define SDK_TOOL_NAMES constants

Create or add to `packages/shared/src/constants.ts`:

```typescript
/** Well-known SDK tool names used in JSONL transcript parsing. */
export const SDK_TOOL_NAMES = {
  SKILL: 'Skill',
  ASK_USER_QUESTION: 'AskUserQuestion',
  TODO_WRITE: 'TodoWrite',
  TASK_CREATE: 'TaskCreate',
  TASK_UPDATE: 'TaskUpdate',
} as const;
```

Export from `packages/shared/src/index.ts` (or the appropriate barrel). If `constants.ts` already exists, add to it. If not, create it and add an export entry.

### 2. Extract `applyToolResult()` helper in transcript-parser.ts

The code at lines 164-181 duplicates tool result application for `toolCallMap` and `toolCallPartMap`. Extract:

```typescript
import { SDK_TOOL_NAMES } from '@dorkos/shared/constants';
// or wherever the constants are exported from

/**
 * Apply a tool result to a tool call record, including answer parsing for AskUserQuestion.
 *
 * @param tc - The tool call or tool call part to update
 * @param resultText - The extracted result text
 * @param sdkAnswers - Optional SDK-provided answers for question tools
 * @internal Exported for testing only.
 */
export function applyToolResult(
  tc: HistoryToolCall | ToolCallPart | undefined,
  resultText: string,
  sdkAnswers?: Record<string, string>,
): void {
  if (!tc) return;
  tc.result = resultText;
  if (
    tc.toolName === SDK_TOOL_NAMES.ASK_USER_QUESTION &&
    tc.questions &&
    !tc.answers
  ) {
    tc.answers = sdkAnswers
      ? mapSdkAnswersToIndices(sdkAnswers, tc.questions as QuestionItem[])
      : parseQuestionAnswers(resultText, tc.questions as QuestionItem[]);
  }
}
```

Replace lines 164-181 with:
```typescript
if (block.type === 'tool_result' && block.tool_use_id) {
  hasToolResult = true;
  const resultText = extractToolResultContent(block.content);
  applyToolResult(toolCallMap.get(block.tool_use_id), resultText, sdkAnswers);
  applyToolResult(toolCallPartMap.get(block.tool_use_id), resultText, sdkAnswers);
}
```

### 3. Extract `emitPendingCommand()` helper in transcript-parser.ts

Duplicated at lines 196-209 and 248-261. Extract:

```typescript
/**
 * Create a user message for a pending slash command.
 *
 * @param cmd - The pending command with name and args
 * @param uuid - The message UUID from the JSONL line
 * @returns A HistoryMessage with role 'user' and messageType 'command'
 * @internal Exported for testing only.
 */
export function buildCommandMessage(
  cmd: { commandName: string; commandArgs: string },
  uuid?: string,
): HistoryMessage {
  const displayContent = cmd.commandArgs
    ? `${cmd.commandName} ${cmd.commandArgs}`
    : cmd.commandName;
  return {
    id: uuid || crypto.randomUUID(),
    role: 'user',
    content: displayContent,
    messageType: 'command',
    commandName: cmd.commandName,
    commandArgs: cmd.commandArgs || undefined,
  };
}
```

Replace both duplicate blocks with:
```typescript
if (pendingCommand) {
  messages.push(buildCommandMessage(pendingCommand, parsed.uuid));
  pendingCommand = null;
  continue;
}
```

### 4. Replace magic strings throughout transcript-parser.ts

Replace all magic tool name strings with `SDK_TOOL_NAMES` constants:
- `'Skill'` -> `SDK_TOOL_NAMES.SKILL`
- `'AskUserQuestion'` -> `SDK_TOOL_NAMES.ASK_USER_QUESTION`
- `'TodoWrite'` -> `SDK_TOOL_NAMES.TODO_WRITE`
- `'TaskCreate'` -> `SDK_TOOL_NAMES.TASK_CREATE`
- `'TaskUpdate'` -> `SDK_TOOL_NAMES.TASK_UPDATE`

Also check `build-task-event.ts` and `task-reader.ts` for the same magic strings.

### 5. Unit Tests

Add to `apps/server/src/services/__tests__/transcript-parser.test.ts`:

```typescript
describe('applyToolResult', () => {
  it('sets result on tool call', () => {
    const tc: Partial<HistoryToolCall> = { toolName: 'SomeTool' };
    applyToolResult(tc as HistoryToolCall, 'the result');
    expect(tc.result).toBe('the result');
  });

  it('does nothing when tc is undefined', () => {
    expect(() => applyToolResult(undefined, 'result')).not.toThrow();
  });

  it('parses answers for AskUserQuestion tool', () => {
    const tc: Partial<HistoryToolCall> = {
      toolName: 'AskUserQuestion',
      questions: [{ question: 'Q1?', options: ['A', 'B'] }] as any,
    };
    applyToolResult(tc as HistoryToolCall, 'A');
    expect(tc.answers).toBeDefined();
  });
});

describe('buildCommandMessage', () => {
  it('creates command message with args', () => {
    const msg = buildCommandMessage({ commandName: '/test', commandArgs: 'arg1' }, 'uuid-1');
    expect(msg.role).toBe('user');
    expect(msg.content).toBe('/test arg1');
    expect(msg.messageType).toBe('command');
    expect(msg.commandName).toBe('/test');
    expect(msg.id).toBe('uuid-1');
  });

  it('creates command message without args', () => {
    const msg = buildCommandMessage({ commandName: '/help', commandArgs: '' });
    expect(msg.content).toBe('/help');
    expect(msg.commandArgs).toBeUndefined();
  });
});
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- `applyToolResult()` correctly applies results to both `HistoryToolCall` and `ToolCallPart` types
- `applyToolResult()` handles `undefined` input gracefully
- `buildCommandMessage()` produces correct message shape with and without args
- `SDK_TOOL_NAMES` constants are used instead of magic strings in transcript-parser.ts
- The parser's behavior is identical before and after refactoring (all existing tests pass)
- No new exports beyond the helper functions and constants (internal helpers marked `@internal`)
